<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>7 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS SPICER PS110-7, PS145-7 - REASSEMBLE - SHIFTER HOUSING</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="assemble" graphiccount="4">
        <title>SHIFTER HOUSING</title>
        <para>Refer to
            <hotlnk document="s13016_11.xml" xrefid="f1301604">Figure 4</hotlnk>and
            <hotlnk document="s13016_11.xml" xrefid="f1301605">Figure 5</hotlnk>.
        </para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lubricate all parts prior to reassembly. Refer to GROUP 10 - LUBRICATION in the CTS-5000
                Master Service Manual for recommended lubricants. Clean the cover, then install the springs, poppets,
                and interlocks (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301694">Figure 94</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301694" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301694" filename="../figg13/G1301694.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 94. Install Springs, Poppets, and Interlocks</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Reassemble the forks and brackets (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301695">Figure 95</hotlnk>). Tighten the setscrews to 26 to 32 ft-lbs. (35 to 43 N&#8226;m).
                Tighten the 2nd-3rd bracket bolts to 13 to 18 ft-lbs. (17 to 24 N&#8226;m).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301695" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301695" filename="../figg13/G1301695.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 95. Re-assemble Forks and Brackets</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place the fork assemblies into the case (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301696">Figure 96</hotlnk>). Secure them with the retainer straps. Tighten the strap
                bolts to 34 to 41 ft-lbs. (46 to 56 N&#8226;m). Move each rod in the cover to confirm that it is moving
                freely.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301696" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301696" filename="../figg13/G1301696.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 96. Place Fork Assemblies Into Case</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the oil trough (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301697">Figure 97</hotlnk>). Tighten the bolts to 34 to 41 ft-lbs. (46 to 56 N&#8226;m).
                Check the cover for correct functioning by shifting one fork into gear. If all interlocks were installed
                correctly, none of the other forks will shift into gear.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301697" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301697" filename="../figg13/G1301697.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 97. Install Oil Trough</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
